content: 'I'm Professor of Distributed Systems at the University of Cambridge Computer Laboratory and, post-retirement, Director of Research. I lectured systems courses such as "Concurrent Systems", "Operating Systems", "Distributed Systems" and "Computer Architecture". Author of "Concurrent Systems" Addison Wesley, 1st edition 1993, 2nd edition 1998, which in 2002/3 evolved into edition 3 for the Open University's "Software systems and their development (M301)" and "Operating Systems: Concurrent and distributed software design" with Tim Harris.
Label: I

content: 'I was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of the Open University in 2013 - conferred in Ely cathedral on June 1st: Eulogy and Acceptance.
Label: I

content: 'I'm a Fellow of Jesus College and Director of Studies in Computer Science. Supervision arrangements are summarised at http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~jmb25/supervisions.
Label: I

content: 'I'm a Fellow of the IEEE and a Fellow of the British Computer Society. I was elected to the IEEE Computer Society's Board of Governors for 2002-2004 and 2005-2007. I was founding Editor in Chief of IEEE Distributed Systems Online (DS Online), which was extended from 2008 to become Computing Now, see: http://www.computer.org/portal/web/computingnow.
Label: I

content: 'Current projects are winter trees in low sunlight and the explosion of may blossom and cow parsley in spring.
